headline: S&P 500's GE Aerospace Is IBD Stock Of The Day, In Buy Zone Following Recent Earnings
summary: GE Aerospace is Monday's IBD Stock Of The Day, as the S&P 500 component continues to show signs of strength coming out of earnings last week with several price target hikes Monday.  Last week, GE Aerospace beat third-quarter expectations, and the stock hit record highs, as it reported a 44% increase in earnings while revenue jumped 26%.  GE Aerospace makes and collaborates on various propulsion technologies that are utilized in missile engines.

headline: The ‘Best Boeing Salesman’ Is at Work in Asia. The Stock Is Up.
summary: Boeing  stock rose early Monday, ahead of this week’s earnings report, as President Donald Trump’s arrival in Asia brought more agreements to buy the company’s jets.  The “Best Boeing salesman strikes again,” wrote Jefferies analyst Sheila Kahyaoglu in a Monday report.  Trump is visiting Asia for talks that will culminate in his meeting with China’s President Xi Jinping in South Korea on Thursday.

headline: Airborne Capital Agrees Second Lease with Geosky Airlines
summary: DUBLIN, October 27, 2025--Airborne Capital, a leading global aircraft asset manager, is delighted to announce the placement and delivery on long term lease of a second Boeing B767-300BCF widebody freighter with Geosky Airlines of Georgia. Geosky is an established and growing cargo airline founded in 2017. This latest addition will take its fleet of B767-300BCF to four units.

headline: China's C919 jet faces turbulent skies amid US-China trade tensions
summary: China’s ambition to challenge Boeing and Airbus with its own homegrown passenger jet is running into turbulence, with deliveries of finished aircraft likely to fall far short of its target announced for this year.  The C919 jet -- a single-aisle passenger plane aiming to rival Boeing’s 737 and Airbus’ A320 – is made by state-owned aircraft manufacturer COMAC.  Beijing is showcasing it as evidence of China's technological advancement and progress in self-reliance, though it uses many Western sourced components.
